content.description: Climb up and slightly right on good holds.  Pull past the overlap where the holds thin and establish yourself in the right facing corner.  Continue up and left before the final moves ups and right through the roof.  Watch the rock quality up high.  Some blocks may not remain solid!
content.protection: Glue In Bolts, Lower Off Anchor
content.location: Starts left off the large hole at head height on the right side of the Balcony. One left of Dew Point

content.description: Fun Moves around the steep section.  Start at the nose of the bulge and work up and left before pulling into the steep section.  Finish onto the ledge.  Lower Off Anchor
content.protection: Glue In Bolts, Lower Off Anchor
content.location: Left of the two routes that begin off the "nose bulge" LEFT of the large cave at head height.

content.description: Currently the leftmost route on the "Balcony" area.  Start at a belay bolt near the steep section of the rock right of the right facing corner before the balcony drops off.  Pull pockets on steep rock into some nice crimps with lots of "flint" intrusions.  A few more moves up into the wet looks stuff.  2 bolts plus anchors.  If only it were longer!
content.protection: 2 Glue In Bolts plus belay bolt at start- Lower Off Anchor

content.description: A Short but pleasant little route, perfect for practicing leading or your lowering skills honed on the anchors just left.  Start left of the tree and climb the face until you pull around left into a shallow, left facing corner.  Reach the anchors in a few more moves.  Lower.NOTE!!!  DO NOT climb above these anchors!!  There is a sloping ledge with all sorts of loose debris up there.  Access to that ledge is pending future development....
content.protection: Glue in Bolts, Lower Off Anchor
content.location: Walk 50' left of Old 5.7 beginning left of the tree.

content.description: More fun short but sweet pulling off the middle of the Balcony.
content.protection: Glue In Bolts, Lower Off Anchor

content.description: The rightmost section of Med School wall that contains a few short climbs. Basically the slab of rock between the vertical French Sport Anchor (2x Stainless Biners) on the Left and a large tree at the base nearly into Old Testament on the Right.Above the base wall sits a medium sized ledge.  The "Balcony".  Sort of a right extension of Debridement or the left most part of OT this elevated area has several short but sweet climbs off of it.  Access is via "Dew Point" on the right (base of OT) or the short lead section into "I Hate Cat Claw".  Please DO NOT climb "First Time" to gain access.  There are LOTS of loose rocks on the slope over there.
